{
  "stem": "39.2",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "After then, we got the daily bread portion, which was like approximately two slices of bread would be today, but more like sawdust.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Very seldom, occasionally we got some little rotten cheese.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "Then we didn't do anything because, as I told you, Auschwitz was no working camp.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "It was extermination camp.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "So we were just sitting on the ground talking to each other, sometimes not even talking.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And the conversation was about family, about freedom, about food, about variety of foods because we were so very, very hungry.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "In the afternoon, again, the same roll call for many, many, hours.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "Again, counted, recounted, from the smallest official until Irma Grese had counted us, and then we got dinner.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "Dinner was a very thin soup.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "Each line of five, we had one bowl.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "Of course, there was no spoon or anything like that.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And we were drinking, each five of us from the same bowl, counting again the sips to make sure that everyone has approximately about the same amount of soup.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "Then we didn't do anything again.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "Other thing in Auschwitz, the humiliation.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "We were reminded with words, with facts, all the time, that we are not human beings.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "We are much less than a bug and what you can step in a second.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "Well, what-- I have the cleanest memories still in my mind of the humiliations, which I am going to tell you.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "It is the outhouse.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "Outhouse was a very big barrack.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "There were many, many seats next to each other, and there were very many rows of seats.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
